10/12/2004
TIRANA, Albania -- Turkish Labour and Social Security Minister Murat Basesgioglu said Thursday (9 December) that Albania and Turkey would sign a protocol for co-operation in labour and the social field on Friday. Visiting Tirana, Basesgioglu met on Thursday with President Alfred Moisiu, Deputy Prime Minister Namik Dokle and Labour Minister Engjell Bejtja. 
In other news Thursday, Moisiu met with visiting Croatian counterpart Stipe Mesic. They agreed that bilateral ties should be strengthened, in light of their countries' common goal of EU integration. (HINA, Anadolu Agency, ATA - 09/12/04)
